# Supported types: feat, fix, chore, refactor, perf, remove, revert, docs, test, style, build, ci
# Example: feat(core): add user authentication

<type>[scope][!]: <short summary>

# Conventional Commit (international standard: conventionalcommits.org)
# Use English type keywords only (global convention for tooling)
#
# Common types:
#   feat      → new feature (minor version bump)
#   fix       → bug fix (patch version bump)
#   docs      → documentation only
#   style     → formatting, no code change
#   refactor  → code change, no behavior change
#   perf      → performance improvement
#   test      → adding/fixing tests
#   build     → build system or dependencies
#   ci        → CI configuration
#   chore     → maintenance (no user impact)
#   revert    → revert previous commit
#   remove    → removed functionality
#
# Add ! after type/scope for breaking changes (major version bump)
# Example: feat(api)!: remove deprecated endpoints

<body – WHAT changed and WHY>

BREAKING CHANGE: <explanation if applicable – or delete this line>

# Standard git trailers:
# Co-authored-by: Name <email@example.com>
# Closes #123
